claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table of solicited local and systemic adverse events (e.g., pain, redness, fatigue, headache, muscle pain, joint pain, shivers/chills, nausea, fever) with percentage values for Flublok and comparator vaccines, accompanied by footnotes on study population and severity grading. does not support the claim - the image only presents adverse event data and contains no information on hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per strain in Flublok or standard-dose vaccines
